<TITLE> BDR, BSF acknowledge 'mutual concerns' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 New Delhi, Mar 11 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh and India border forces have vowed to strengthen mutual cooperation and "be sensitive to each other's concerns" in line with the joint communique issued during prime minister Sheikh Hasina's to New Delhi earlier this year. Bangladesh Rifles and India's Border Security Force made the vow on Thursday, the concluding day of t the four-day Indo-Bangladesh Border Coordination Conference in New Delhi, which focused on movement of terrorists along the borders. The Bangladesh Rifles (BDR) chief Maj Gen Md Mainul Islam led the 19-member delegation from Bangladesh; while the Indian side was led by the Director General of the country's Border Security Force (BSF) Raman Srivastava. bdn
